HEADWORD: Thermojunction
<hw>Ther`mo*junc"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A junction of two dissimilar conductors used to
produce a thermoelectric current, as in one form of pyrometer; a
thermocouple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

